verview

A 4-to-2 encoder is a combinational logic circuit that encodes 4 input lines into 2 binary outputs. At a time, only one input should be active. The encoder outputs the binary code corresponding to the active input line.

Truth Table
Input (d3 d2 d1 d0)	Output (q1 q0)
0001	00
0010	01
0100	10
1000	11
Others	Undefined
Boolean Equations

q0 = d3 + d1

q1 = d3 + d2

Verilog Files

encoder4_2.v – Encoder module

encoder4_2tb.v – Testbench for simulation

Applications

Digital systems to minimize the number of bits required

Input devices (e.g., keyboards) to encode pressed keys

Microprocessors (used in priority encoders for interrupt handling)
